	"description": "You&#x27;ve probably seen a &quot;back-to-top&quot; button at the bottom-right corner on many\nwebsites when you&#x27;re scrolling around. Clicking on that button takes you back to\nthe top of the page. \n\nThis is a great feature to have on any website, and today we are going to see\nhow to build it with nothing but HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. \n\nWe are also going to look at how to add a page progress bar, one at the top\nwhich will increase in progress as we scroll down and decrease as we scroll up. \n\nNote that you can a",
